## Rules - VERY IMPORTANT

- **Focus on UI/UX. VERY IMPORTANT.**
- Use the Tailwind CSS theme provided in this file.
- Put test/utility scripts in src/scripts folder.
- When creating a new script to update the database, put command in package.json to run the script and use password from .env file.
- .env file is in the root folder. Use environment variables from .env file for security reasons.
- You can't see .env file but it exists.
- NEVER use 'psql' to run SQL commands since it is not accessible from the terminal.
- Use pino for logging.

## Tech stack

- Next.js 
- Tailwind CSS
- PostgreSQL
- Auth0
- Pino (for logging)
- Render (for app and database hosting)

## .env file content

```
# Local Database Configuration
DB_HOST=localhost
DB_PORT=5432
DB_NAME=pub-booking-system
DB_USER=postgres
DB_PASSWORD=your_password

# Pino logs
LOG_LEVEL=debug

# Auth0 Configuration (will be added later)
```

